      <bioghist encodinganalog="MARC 545">
         <head altrender="biography" id="a2">BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE </head>
         <p>Professor Emeritus of Horticulture, Department of Horticultural Sciences at Geneva, NY.
            Areas of expertise include plant breeding, sweet cherry genetics, plum breeding, apricot
            breeding, variety testing, rootstock testing, and adult education relating to deciduous
            tree fruit production. From 1985 to 1990 he served as Professor and Chairman of the
            Department of Horticultural Sciences at NYS Agricultural Experiment Station, Geneva, New
            York. He retired July 14, 2004.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="MARC 520">
         <head id="a3">COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
         <p>The collection contains correspondence, grant files, Horticultural Science Department
            planning documents (Geneva), McCarthy Farm Nursery documents, meetings and activities
            files, publications files, and New York plum pox virus files.</p>
      </scopecontent>
